''' Himalayan Silver Fir forests''' is a [[plant community]] and [[cconifer forest]] [[habitat]] type in the [[Western Himalayan subalpine conifer forests|Western Himalayan subalpine conifer forests ecoregion]] of the [[Temperate coniferous forests]] [[Biome]].

The forest's vegetation is dominated by the [[Abies pindrow|''Abies pindrow'' (Himalayan Silver Fir)]] species of [[conifer]] trees.

==Geography==
It is located in the [[Western Himalayas]] region of the [[Himalayan Range]] System in southern Asia.

Himalayan Silver Fir Forests are found from  the [[Gandak River]] region in [[Nepal]], through the higher elevations of [[northwestern India]], to montane northern [[Pakistan]].{{cn|date=July 2015}}

